Task
Minimum element of an array
Write a minInArray function that takes arr as an argument and returns the minimum element of the array.
Use a loop in your solution. The use of the Math.min () method is not permitted.
Example:
• the minInArray ([3, 4, 8, 1]) function must return 1;
• the minInArray ([11, 12) function must return 11;
• the minInArray ([1, 1]) function must return 1;
• the minInArray ([]) function must return undefined.

Solution
function minInArray (arr) {
  let min = arr [0];
  if (arr.length === 0) return undefined;
  for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
   if (arr [i] <min) {
    min = arr [i];
    }
    }
    return min;
    }
